Compute the joint cumulative distribution function (CDF) for the random variable $X = Y_1 - Y_2$, given the joint probability density function (PDF):
\[
f(y_1, y_2) = 
\begin{cases}
e^{-y_1}, &\quad 0 \leq y_2 \leq y_1 < +\infty \\
0, &\quad \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
\]

Given the joint probability density function of random variables $X$ and $Y$:
\[
f_{X,Y}(x,y) = \begin{cases}
\frac{1}{y}, & 0 < x < y, \ 0< y< 1 \\
0, & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
\]
find the variance of $X$. Use the law of total variance: \(V(X)=E(V(X|Y))+V(E(X|Y))\).

A machine consists of two components with lifetimes described by the joint density function:
\[
f(x,y)=
\begin{cases}
1/50, & \text{for }x>0,y>0,x+y<10 \\
0, & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
\]
The machine operates until both components fail. Calculate the expected operational time of the machine.

Calculate the probability \( P(X+Y \leq 1) \) given the joint density function:
\[
f(x,y)= \begin{cases}
\frac{4x^3}{y^3} & \text{if $0<x<1, x<y$}\\
0 & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
\]

Given the joint density function of the two-dimensional variable \((X, Y)\):
\[
f(x,y) = \begin{cases} 
2x^2 & \text{if } -1 < x < 1 \text{ and } 0 < y < |x| \\
0 & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
\]
Compute the conditional expected value \(E(X-Y \mid X+Y = -0.5)\).

Given the joint probability density function:
\[
f_{X,Y}(x,y) = \begin{cases} 
ye^{-xy-y} & \text{if } x > 0, y > 0 \\
0 & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
\]
Calculate the distribution of the product $XY$. Assume $X$ and $Y$ are dependent random variables.

Given the joint probability density function of the lifetimes of two circuits $C1$ and $C2$ in an electronic device:
\[
f(x,y) = \begin{cases}
\frac{24}{(x+y)^4},  & \text{x,y > 1} \\
0, & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
\]
where $X$ and $Y$ are continuous random variables representing the lifetimes of $C1$ and $C2$, respectively. Calculate the expected value of the time until the device is completely corrupted.

Given the joint distribution of random variables $X$ and $Y$:
\[
f(x, y) = \begin{cases} 
2, & 0 < x \leq y < 1, \\
0, & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
\]
Determine the correlation coefficient between $X$ and $Y$. \( \rho(X, Y) \)

Compute the covariance \( \text{Cov}(X, Y) \) for the random variables \( X \) and \( Y \) with the joint probability density function given by:
\[
f(x,y) = \begin{cases}
\left(\frac{2e^{-2x}}{x}\right) & \text{, $0 < y < x <  ∞$} \\
0 & \text{, elsewhere}
\end{cases}
\]

Let \(X\) and \(Y\) be random variables with the joint probability density function given by:
\[
f_{X,Y}(x,y) = \begin{cases} 
0.25ye^{-y} & \text{if } 0 \leq |x| \leq y \\
0 & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
\]
Find the conditional density \(f_{X|Y = y}(x)\) and identify the conditional distribution \(X|_{Y = y}\). Then, use the law of total expectation to find \(E[X^2]\).

Calculate the conditional probability $P(A|B)$, where event $A$ is defined as $x<y$ and event $B$ is defined as $x<2y$. The joint probability distribution of $(x,y)$ is given by:

$$F(x,y) = \begin{cases} 
xye^{-(x+y)} & \text{if} ~~~~ x,y>0\\ 
0 & \text{elsewhere} 
\end{cases}$$

Determine $P(A|B)$ using the given joint distribution.

Calculate the covariance between the random variables X and Y given their joint density function:

$$
f(x, y) = \begin{cases}
e^{-y}, & \text{if } 0 < x < y \\
0, & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
$$

Given a prime number \( p \) and a natural number \( n \) such that \( p \geqslant n \geqslant 3 \), let the set \( A \) consist of sequences of length \( n \) with elements drawn from the set \( \{1, 2, \cdots, p-1\} \). For any two sequences \((x_{1}, x_{2}, \cdots, x_{n})\) and \((y_{1}, y_{2}, \cdots, y_{n})\) from set \( A \), there must exist three distinct positive integers \( k, l, m \) such that \( x_{k} 
eq y_{k}, x_{l} 
eq y_{l}, x_{m} 
eq y_{m} \). Determine the maximum number of elements in set \( A \).
